%% Diagram: Resumable upload state machine for a pending file revision
%% Type: state
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Detected: filesystem watcher fires<br/>or scan picks up change

    Detected --> Chunked: split into 4 MiB blocks
    Chunked --> Hashed: SHA-256 each block
    Hashed --> Committing: send blocklist to metadata
    Committing --> Uploading: server returns missing hashes
    Committing --> Committed: 200 OK, no missing blocks (full dedup hit)
    Uploading --> Recommitting: all PutBlocks acked
    Recommitting --> Committed: SFJ row appended, JID assigned
    Committed --> [*]

    Detected --> Detected: file changed again<br/>(coalesce, restart from chunked)

    Chunked --> Hashed
    Hashed --> Hashed: re-hash on partial read

    Uploading --> Uploading: per-block retry on 5xx / network error<br/>(idempotent PutBlock)
    Uploading --> Hashed: server says hash mismatch<br/>(client-side memory corruption)

    Committing --> Hashed: cursor stale / namespace moved<br/>re-resolve and retry
    Recommitting --> Uploading: server reports new missing block<br/>(GC race or recent purge)

    state Crashes <<fork>>
    Detected --> Crashes
    Chunked --> Crashes
    Hashed --> Crashes
    Uploading --> Crashes
    Committing --> Crashes
    Recommitting --> Crashes

    Crashes --> Resume: restart, read on-disk state +<br/>SQLite cursor
    Resume --> Chunked: only file path persisted
    Resume --> Uploading: blocklist persisted, some PutBlocks done
    Resume --> Recommitting: blocklist + all PutBlocks done
